		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Whispers of Wrath",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>The inciter chooses a creature it can see within 20 feet, attempting to incite the wrath in the creature's heart. Target creature must attempt at a @Check[will|dc:25] save. The inciter can't use Whisper of Wrath again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Duration]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> the creature is unaffected and immune to Whisper of Wrath for 1 hour.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> the creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 1}.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> the creature is stupefied 1 and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.yblD8fOR1J8rDwEQ]{Confused} until the end of its next turn.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> the creature falls in a mindless rage. The creature gains the effect of a barbarian's Rage ability (without the temporary hit points) and is confused for 1 minute. If the creature had abilities that triggers while in rage (like some barbarian abilities) or that requires the creature to be in rage, the creature can use these abilities and effects.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.monster-homebrewery.effects.Item.CcVP3fkM1VaWsiJj]{Effect: Whispers of Wrath (Critical Failure)}</p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
				"publication": {
